In addition to other articles, see the following:

## Civil Administration

> –Administrative Autonomy, Superior Authorities, Captaincies, Donations, Grantees, Governors, General Assemblies, Order of Christ, Administrative Organization, Settlement, Colonization, Representation in Courts, and Sesmaria;

## Ecclesiastical Administration

> –Archbishopric, Bishops and the name of each prelate, Chapter, Collegiate Churches, Bishop's Constitutions, Convents, Diocese, Parishes, Jesuits, New Monastery, Order of Christ, and Seraphic Order; Fiscal Administration–Customs, Contributions, Treasury Board, Fiscal Organization, and Revenue and Expenses;

## Judicial Administration

> –Judicial Administration, Jurisdictions, Land Registry Offices, Grantees, Judges, Judicial Organization, and Police;

## Military Administration

> –Shooting Range, Military Commanders, Grantees, Fortifications, Military Garrison, War (Great), Militia, Occupations, Military Organization, Police, Unknown Soldier, and Surprise; Municipal Administration

> –Annals of the Municipality, Municipal Chambers, Captaincies, Councils, Charters, Municipalities, and Administrative Organization; Parish Administration Parishes, Parish Councils, and Administrative Organization.
